## 3. Hidden Halo Settings — Best of Both Worlds

Hidden halo is the only halo configuration that works correctly for princess cut. The halo sits below the table, not around the perimeter — so the square geometry reads cleanly from above.

**[Petite Hidden Halo Solitaire Plus in 14k Yellow Gold — $1,255](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/petite-hidden-halo-solitaire-plus-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-item-192506?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
The premier hidden halo for princess cut. Looks like a solitaire from above, reveals sparkle from the side. Farzana's pick for buyers who want halo without the round-look buyer trap.

**[Crown Pavé Hidden Halo in 14K Yellow Gold (JA) — $1,970](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/crown-pave-hidden-halo-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-by-james-allen-item-315156?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
Crown-set hidden halo with pavé on the setting arms.

**[Crown Pavé Hidden Halo in 14K Rose Gold (JA) — $1,970](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/crown-pave-hidden-halo-diamond-engagement-ring-in-14k-rose-gold-by-james-allen-item-315149?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)**
Same crown hidden halo in rose gold.

> **Round halo vs hidden halo:** A round halo places a circular ring of diamonds around the princess perimeter, framing it as a round shape from above. This is the most common buyer trap in princess cut ring shopping — see [Princess Cut Halo Engagement Ring](https://diamondcritics.com/princess-cut-halo-engagement-ring/) for the complete analysis.

